</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2A1206B1F8435609E6FC474D6AE66993" pageId="21" pageNumber="84" type="notes">
<paragraph id="FE3D773545AF254001F6889720096B7B" pageId="21" pageNumber="84">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC390750BEC7FEE6C2E83FC8B79092FC" pageId="21" pageNumber="84">
<bibRefCitation id="7C9239DCAA57783BDF65843868F7043B" author="De la Rua, P" journalOrPublisher="Apidologie" pageId="25" pageNumber="88" pagination="699 - 708" title="Molecular characterization and population structure of Apismellifera from Madeira and the Azores." url="https://doi.org/10.1051/apido:2006044" volume="37" year="2006">
De la 
<normalizedToken id="0EEEDC67B3B57B862005D3B246ED4C52" originalValue="Rúa">Rua</normalizedToken>
et al. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
analysed genetic diversity of Azorean honeybees and found a comparably low number of mitochondrial haplotypes, some of them shared with Madeiran honeybees, other probably recent introductions from the mainland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
